411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, Mr A.A.Adesanya granted the defendant bail in the sum of N1 million with two sureties in like sum. He adjourned the case until Feb. 4 for mention. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. A 31-year-old man, Sunday Ibe, was on Tuesday, arraigned in Lagos for allegedly receiving N6.8 million worth of stolen phones at Computer Village in Ikeja. July 30, 2019 In "News" A 40- year-old businessman, Peter Williams, was Monday, arraigned before an Ikeja Magistrate Court, for allegedly receiving a 40-feet empty Container valued at N1.5million. October 2, 2013 In "Crime Guard" LAGOS—Three traders at Alaba International Market, Ojo, Lagos, have been arraigned by the police for allegedly breaking into a store in the market and stealing rolls of speaker wire valued at N16. 6 million, being the property of Ugo Ventures. September 13, 2016 In "News"